SIDEBAR TITLE: Turning spectators into participants
CLIENT: WTT Singapore Smash
DATE: 30 Jan – 9 Feb 2025
LOCATION: Singapore Sports Hub

BODY:
  ### Infrastructure and Experience Design
  KIN conceptualised and implemented innovative elements to distinguish
  WTT Singapore Smash 2025 from previous editions. The introduction of
  self-service fan booths and free-to-play tables was a strategic decision
  to transform passive spectators into engaged participants. Working with
  trusted partners — A-media, DMC, and Mediapix — every touchpoint reflected
  the event's premium positioning.

  ### Operational Excellence
  Anticipating record attendance, KIN implemented robust crowd management
  systems. The team worked closely with WTT and venue management to handle
  the significant increase in patron numbers compared to previous years.
  This collaborative approach proved crucial in managing many sold-out
  sessions and ensuring timely seating arrangements for all attendees.

  ### Sustainable Event Management
  Environmental responsibility was integrated into planning from day one.
  KIN made conscious decisions to use green ink for branding materials and
  repurposed carpentry elements from previous years — demonstrating a
  commitment to sustainable event management without compromising on quality
  or experience.

  ### Rising to the Challenge
  When faced with larger-than-expected crowds, the team implemented efficient
  seating protocols that ensured smooth crowd flow without compromising the
  guest experience. The addition of a Player Party to this year's programme
  required careful integration into the existing event framework while
  maintaining focus on core deliverables.

  ### Key Learnings
  The success of WTT Singapore Smash 2025 provided valuable insights for
  future large-scale sporting events: the importance of staying adaptable
  to emerging trends, the value of going beyond standard service
  expectations, and the benefits of integrating sustainable practices from
  the planning stage.

